</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E1150D16A3FCFF54AEBDE2FC2A0CFBF6" blockId="178.[189,1399,939,1071]" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">
<taxonomicName id="26AA7695A3FCFF54AEBDE2FC2A3CFC1C" authorityName="Zahniser &amp; Dietrich" authorityYear="2013" box="[189,354,939,965]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Arrugada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linnavuorii">
<emphasis id="D3DED104A3FCFF54AEBDE2FC2A3CFC1C" box="[189,354,939,965]" italics="true" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">A. linnavuorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="26AA7695A3FCFF54AC05E2FC287BFC1C" authority="Osborn, 1924" authorityName="Osborn" authorityYear="1924" box="[517,805,939,965]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Arrugada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis id="D3DED104A3FCFF54AC05E2FC2927FC1C" box="[517,633,939,965]" italics="true" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">A. rugosa</emphasis>
Osborn, 1924
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="26AA7695A3FCFF54AD63E2FC2FD2FC1C" authority="(Osborn, 1924)" baseAuthorityName="Osborn" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[867,1164,939,965]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Arrugada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="D3DED104A3FCFF54AD63E2FC2893FC1C" box="[867,973,939,965]" italics="true" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">A. affinis</emphasis>
(Osborn, 1924)
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the pygofer but can be distinguished from them by the medially unproduced head (produced in 
<taxonomicName id="26AA7695A3FCFF54AB03E2982E28FC31" authorityName="Osborn" authorityYear="1924" box="[1283,1398,975,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Arrugada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis id="D3DED104A3FCFF54AB03E2982E28FC31" box="[1283,1398,975,1001]" italics="true" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">A. rugosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="26AA7695A3FCFF54AEEFE2A52A09FBD5" baseAuthorityName="Osborn" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[239,343,1010,1036]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Arrugada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="D3DED104A3FCFF54AEEFE2A52A09FBD5" box="[239,343,1010,1036]" italics="true" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">A. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the shape of the aedeagus which, is longer, more bowed, and apex not spinose in the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A9B05E9DA3FCFF54AEBDE50129E4FB1B" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E1150D16A3FCFF54AEBDE5012A1AFBA9" blockId="178.[189,324,1110,1136]" box="[189,324,1110,1136]" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">
<heading id="BA5DBA7AA3FCFF54AEBDE5012A1AFBA9" bold="true" box="[189,324,1110,1136]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" reason="3">
